race.comment: THEN WHAT TIME (3) was comfortably accounted for when sixth last time out over 1609m at Colonial Downs, beaten 7 lengths. That followed a win at Colonial Downs at the previous outing. Finds a suitable race and can get the job done. BRINDANO (9) progressed nicely last time out when he did his best work late to finish just 1.5 lengths from the winner in third over 1308m at Timonium. Looks well placed so expect another big run. GREAT ARTIST (12) was given time to settle from an outside draw last time then wound up strongly in the straight for an eye-catching second over 1106m at this track (Turf). Will be tough to stop again. AGENT KELLY (16) ran a better race last start to finish a close second over 1106m at this track after missing the placings at the previous appearance. Another forward showing is anticipated. Something for the Multiples: NEW YORK STRONG (4) MAMBA MINDSET (5) GOTTA HAVE A GUY (8)
